🚀 Data Visualization Project | Transforming Raw Data into Actionable Insights 📊

I'm excited to share my latest Data Visualization Project, where I analyzed a dataset of 200 books and transformed raw data into meaningful visual insights using Python and business intelligence tools.

This project demonstrates how effective visualizations can simplify complex data, uncover hidden trends, and support data-driven decision-making.

🔍 Project Highlights

📚 Analyzed a dataset of 200 books across multiple categories.
📊 Performed Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to understand data patterns and relationships.
📈 Created interactive and insightful visualizations using Matplotlib and Seaborn.
📉 Designed charts to analyze category distribution, price trends, ratings, stock availability, and feature correlations.
📌 Built a dashboard concept suitable for Power BI and Tableau.
💡 Generated business recommendations based on data-driven insights.

📊 Visualizations Included

✅ Category-wise Book Count
✅ Average Price by Category
✅ Book Price Distribution
✅ Rating Distribution
✅ Price vs Rating Analysis
✅ Top 10 Most Expensive Books
✅ Stock Distribution
✅ Correlation Heatmap
✅ Dashboard with KPI Cards

🛠️ Tools & Technologies

- Python
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Tableau
- Power BI
- Jupyter Notebook

📈 Key Business Insights

✔️ Programming and AI books dominate the inventory.
✔️ AI books have the highest average selling price.
✔️ Most books are priced in the medium price range.
✔️ Higher prices do not always result in higher ratings.
✔️ Correlation analysis helps identify relationships between price, ratings, and stock levels.
✔️ Interactive dashboards enable faster and more informed business decisions.

This project strengthened my skills in Data Cleaning, Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), Data Visualization, Dashboard Design, Data Storytelling, and Business Analytics.

